TopicTitle: My rocket breaks in half and struts have no effect

Articles.Content: But KJR still works only up to 1.3
Did you actually read the last couple pages of the KJR thread, or are you just going off the thread title?  I'm using KJR in 1.6.1 just fine.
What does the ship look like?

3 hours ago, Jaime said:

Try autostrut under advanced tweakables

Does not work either! In fact, I autostrutted the whole rocked, also turned rigid attachment on.

It breaks loose between the fairing and the fuel tank.

A glitchy joint Restock has there.

Just now, Gapone said:

Does not work either! In fact, I autostrutted the whole rocked, also turned rigid attachment on.

It breaks loose between the fairing and the fuel tank.

A glitchy joint Restock has there.

can we see your craft file then

5 minutes ago, Jaime said:

can we see your craft file then

It's a modified @Temstar's Nova 2.

I pretty much fixed the issue by placing the tank on the decoupler with part clipping on and then shifting it back.

But just paste this into .CRAFT file then reattach the orange fuel tank. It should break there once you attempt to perform a gravity turn.

Pretty much somehow a restock issue, never had problems before.

That might cause complaints from people trying to read the forum on a mobile device. Pasted log-files have crashed their browsers; craft files are not usually so big but this one is 333kB.  Maybe edit your post to remove that if you've solved the problem.

Temstar's NOVA-A  is a big lifter below, three big orange tanks above as payload,  and a smaller-diameter probe core between them, shielded by a fairing.   The joints around the probe core would be the weak point, but they are bridged by struts pretty well.  That makes the joint between the fairing and lifter the highest concentration of stress, so it will be the first to fail.  

I added EAS 4 struts from the tips of the boosters to the payload, which make it somewhat less fragile. Then  I turned off gimbal on most of the engines, turned off the reaction wheel, added steerable fins, and turned off all the autostruts, and like how it flies after all that.
